## Conclusion

{% if summary.L_pct_diff < 5.0 -%}
Angular momentum was conserved within {{ "%.2f"|format(summary.L_pct_diff) }}% —
the experimental result supports the Law of Conservation of Angular Momentum.
{% else -%}
The angular momentum difference of {{ "%.2f"|format(summary.L_pct_diff) }}% exceeds the
expected range, suggesting friction losses at the bearing or numerical effects.
{% endif %}

Kinetic energy decreased by {{ "%.2f"|format(summary.KE_pct_loss) }}%, confirming that
this is an **inelastic** rotational collision. Angular momentum can be conserved
while kinetic energy is lost because friction between the disk and
{{ summary.drop_object }} converts kinetic energy into thermal energy without
applying any net external torque to the system.

